  "description": [
    "PAGE FOUR _ FLORIDAS FAVORITE COLORED WEEKLY Office at 1112 NW Third Avenue Miami FloridaTelephone 32236 Plant at 6740 NW 15th AvenueTelephone 32236 Entered as Second Class Matter August 9 1927 at the Post Office at Miami Florida under the act of March 3 1876 H E SIGISMUND REEVES Editor GARTH C REEVES Business Manager ADVERTISING REPRESENTATIVE interstate United Newspapers Incorporated 545 Fifth Ave New York Member of the Associated Negro Press Member of the National Newspaper Publishers Association SUBSCRIPTION RATES ONE YEAR 400 SIX MONTHS 250 THREE MONTHS 150 WE LIKE STEVENSON There as b een a lot of exposure of the conduct and affairs of the two vice presidential candidates Senator Nixon and Senator Sparkman Let us be fair about it neither has a record to boast of especially so when it conies to the Negro cause So let us forget about them and keep our minds on the presidential candidates and the two parties The question uppermost in our minds should be Which administration has done more for the country especially the poorer classes Unless we are blind and deaf we should be able to answer the Democrats and that is the reasoning that Negroes should use"
  ],
